--/|ScriptCards Library: ScriptCards Library pf2espellLib
--/|Author: Zaxbeez
--/|System: Pathfinder Second Edition, Remaster and Legacy
--/|Function: This library provides spell information for pf2e spells, as taken from pf2etools.com, and formats that information in a ScriptCards-Friendly way.
    --/|(I found some descrepincies between pf2etools and Archives of Nethys - I always used the Archive information in these cases.)
--/|Description of Use: In a ScriptCards script, call this library to print the spell information.
    --/|In the main script, call this library with Lib2e_SPELL_FETCH|[token-id],[Spell Name]
    --/|Further modifications can bake in SmartAoE or token modifications aligning with the spell effects (Statusmarker updates, health deduction, condition updates, etc.)
--/|Caveats: There are some spells that cause Afflictions; install the pf2eAfflictionLib library for the information associated with those. 
    
--/|To get the Remastered versions of the spells to print, put any value inside of the following variable.
    --&Remastered|

--/|Set the Format Settings
    --&bodyFontSize|14
    --#bodyfontsize|[&bodyFontSize]px

--/|Set the Reaction, One, Two, Three, and Free Action image settings here
    --&Img_Format|style='position: relative; bottom:3px;' width=[&bodyFontSize]px
    --&Reaction|[img [&Img_Format]]https://i.imgur.com/W2WUxcQ.png[/img]
    --&One_Action|[img [&Img_Format]]https://i.imgur.com/HHjp6RP.png[/img]
    --&Two_Action|[img [&Img_Format]]https://i.imgur.com/WuocaeP.png[/img]
    --&Three_Action|[img [&Img_Format]]https://i.imgur.com/piqYyy6.png[/img]
    --&Free_Action|[img [&Img_Format]]https://i.imgur.com/hiz4szr.png[/img]
        
--:Lib2e_SPELL_FETCH|Token_ID,Spell_Name
    --/|Passed Attributes
        --&t_id|[&reentryval(split,%,0)]
        --&Spell_Directory|[&reentryval(split,%,1)]
    --/|Format Input Spell Name for Library
        --&Spell_Directory|[&Spell_Directory(touppercase)]
        --&Spell_Directory|[&Spell_Directory(replaceall, ,_)]
    --/|Pull Caster data
        --&Ability_Mod|[*S:spell_attack_key_ability]

    -->_[&Spell_Directory]|


--:_SPELL_PRINT|
    --#title|[&Spell_Name]
    --#leftsub|[&Spell_Traditions]
    --#rightsub|[?"[&Spell_Traits]" -inc "cantrip"|Cantrip [&Spell_Level]|Spell [&Spell_Level]]

    --+Action Cost: |[&Casting_Time]
    --?"X[&Spell_Traits]" -ne "X"|>_TRAIT_CHECK;"Traits:";Spell_Traits
    --?"X[&Spell_Range]" -ne "X"|>_RANGE_CHECK;"Range:";Spell_Range
    --?"X[&Spell_Target]" -ne "X"|>_TARGET_CHECK;"Targets:";Spell_Target
    --+Description: |[&Spell_Description]
    --?"X[&Critical_Success]" -ne "X"|>_DEGREE_CHECK;"Critical Success";Critical_Success
    --?"X[&Success]" -ne "X"|>_DEGREE_CHECK;"Success";Success
    --?"X[&Failure]" -ne "X"|>_DEGREE_CHECK;"Failure";Failure
    --?"X[&Critical_Failure]" -ne "X"|>_DEGREE_CHECK;"Critical Failure";Critical_Failure
    --?"X[&Heightened_Effects]" -ne "X"|>_HEIGHTENED_CHECK;"Heightened:";Heightened_Effects
    --+Source|[&Spell_Source],[&Page]
    --X|

--:_TRAIT_CHECK|
    --+[%1%]|[&[%2%]]
    --<|
--:_RANGE_CHECK|
    --+[%1%]|[&[%2%]]
    --<|
--:_TARGET_CHECK|
    --+[%1%]|[&[%2%]]
    --<|            
--:_DEGREE_CHECK|
    --+[%1%]|[&[%2%]]
    --<|
--:_HEIGHTENED_CHECK|
    --+[%1%]|[&[%2%]]
    --<|
--:_ABERRANT_FORM|
--&Spell_Name|Aberrant Form
--&Spell_Source|SoM
--&Remastered|
--&Page|88
--&Spell_Focus|
--&Spell_Level|5
--&Spell_Traits|polymorph, transmutation
--&Spell_Domains|
--&Spell_Subclass|
--&Spell_Traditions|occult
--&Casting_Time|2 actions
--&Spell_Components|Somatic, Verbal
--&Spell_Trigger|
--&Spell_Requirements|
--&Spell_Range|
--&Spell_Area_Type|
--&Spell_Area_Description|
--&Spell_Saving_Throw|
--&Spell_Targets|
--&Spell_Duration|1 minute (Dismiss)
--&Spell_Description|Harnessing the power of vile entities, you transform yourself into a Large aberration. You must have enough space to expand into or the spell is lost. When you cast this spell, choose chuul, gogiteth, gug, or otyugh. While in this form, you gain the aberration trait. You can Dismiss the spell.
You gain the following statistics and abilities regardless of which battle form you choose:
[br]●AC = 18 + your level. Ignore your armor's check penalty and Speed reduction.
[br]●13 temporary Hit Points. Darkvision.
[br]●One or more unarmed melee attacks specific to the battle form you choose, which are the only attacks you can Strike with. You're trained with them. Your attack modifier is +18, and you use the listed damage. These attacks are Strength based (for the purpose of the Enfeebled condition, for example). If your unarmed attack modifier is higher, you can use it instead.
[br]●Athletics modifier of +20, unless your own modifier is higher.
You also gain specific abilities based on the type of aberration you choose:
[br][f[=[&bodyFontSize]+1]\\][b]Chuul[/b][/f] Speed 30 feet, swim 25 feet
[br][b]Melee[/b] [&One_Action] claw (reach (10 feet)), [b]Damage[/b] 2d8+8 bludgeoning, and you can spend an action after a hit to Grab the target.
[br][f[=[&bodyFontSize]+1]\\][b]Gogiteth[/b][/f] Speed 40 feet, climb 30 feet
[br][b]Melee[/b] [&One_Action] jaws, [b]Damage[/b] 2d10+8 piercing, and you can spend an action after a hit to Grab the target
[br][b]Melee[/b] [&One_Action] leg (agile, reach (10 feet)), [b]Damage[/b] 2d6+8 piercing.
[br][f[=[&bodyFontSize]+1]\\][b]Gug[/b][/f] Speed 40 feet, climb 20 feet
[br][b]Melee[/b] [&One_Action] jaws (reach (10 feet)), [b]Damage[/b] 2d12+8 piercing
[br][b]Melee[/b] [&One_Action]
--&Critical_Success|
--&Success|
--&Failure|
--&Critical_Failure|
--&Affliction|
--&Heightened_Effects|Heightened (6th) Your battle form is Huge, and the reach of your attacks increases by 5 feet. You must have space to expand, or the spell is lost. You instead gain AC = 21 + your level, 26 temporary HP, attack modifier +22, damage bonus +13, and Athletics +23.
--&Amp|
--^_SPELL_PRINT|

--:_ABERRANT_WHISPERS|
--&Spell_Name|Aberrant Whispers
--&Spell_Source|[?"X[&Remastered]" -ne "X"|PC2|CRB]
--&Page|[?"X[&Remastered]" -ne "X"|262|402]
--&Spell_Focus|TRUE
--&Spell_Level|3
--&Spell_Traits|[?"X[&Remastered]" -ne "X"|uncommon, auditory, concentrate, focus, mental, sorcerer|uncommon, auditory, enchantment, mental, sorcerer]
--&Spell_Domains|
--&Spell_Subclass|
--&Spell_Traditions|
--&Casting_Time|1 to 3 actions
--&Spell_Components|[?"X[&Remastered]" -ne "X"||Verbal]
--&Spell_Trigger|
--&Spell_Requirements|
--&Spell_Range|
--&Spell_Area_Type|Emanation
--&Spell_Area_Description|5-foot emanation or more
--&Spell_Saving_Throw|Will
--&Spell_Targets|each foe in the area
--&Spell_Duration|1 round
--&Spell_Description|[?"X[&Remastered]" -ne "X"|You utter phrases in an unknown tongue, assaulting the minds of those nearby. Each target must attempt a Will save. Regardless of the result of its save, each target is then temporarily immune for 1 minute. For each additional action you use when casting the spell, increase the emanation's radius by 5 feet.|You utter phrases in an unknown tongue, assaulting the minds of those nearby. Each target must attempt a Will save. Regardless of the result of its save, each target is then temporarily immune for 1 minute. You can increase the number of actions it takes to cast the spell (to a maximum of 3 actions total). For each additional action, increase the emanation's radius by 5 feet, to a maximum of 10 extra feet for 3 actions.]
--&Critical_Success|
--&Success|The target is unaffected.
--&Failure|The target is Stupefied 2.
--&Critical_Failure|The target is Confused.
--&Affliction|
--&Heightened_Effects|Heightened (+3): The initial radius increases by 5 feet.
--&Amp|
--^_SPELL_PRINT|

