--&Spell_Targets|one unattended item or one item you're holding
--&Spell_Duration|until your next daily preparations
--&Spell_Description|You create an illusion that makes an object seem to be something entirely different. When you cast this spell, speak aloud a declarative statement that the target is a different, nonspecific object. Your statement can't presuppose any other facts. For instance, you could claim an object is "a stone" or "an antidote, " but not "the Starstone" or "the antidote to the lethal poison you already drank. " Creatures who previously Observed the target receive an immediate Will save to disbelieve, but on a failure, the illusion temporarily rewrites their memory that the object was something different. A creature who failed their Will save, or didn't already see the item's original form, must Interact with the illusion as normal to receive a Perception check against the Spell DC to disbelieve.
When the spell ends, targets remember the object's true nature, even if they never disbelieved the spell.
