[br][b]Melee[/b] [&One_Action] foot, [b]Damage[/b] 2d8 bludgeoning
[br]You can speak in this form, but you still can't cast a spell or supply verbal components.
[br][f[=[&bodyFontSize]+1]\\][b]Flytrap[/b][/f] Speed 15 feet; resistance 10 to acid
[br][b]Melee[/b] [&One_Action] leaf (reach (10 feet)), [b]Damage[/b] 2d8 piercing, and you can spend an action after a hit to Grab the target.
--&Spell_Description_O|Taking inspiration from verdant creatures, you transform into a Large plant battle form. You must have space to expand into or the spell is lost. When you cast this spell, choose arboreal, flytrap, or shambler. You can substitute a similar specific plant to turn into (such as a pitcher plant instead of a flytrap), but this has no effect on the form's Size or statistics. While in this form, you gain the plant trait. You can Dismiss the spell.
